languages.text: "Я... знаю..." {n}Что-то в голосе Джай ломается. Вам даже кажется, будто слышится скрип: словно старая гайка сошла с резьбы, и ржавый механизм визжит, сопротивляясь насилию.{/n} "Но Торра и ребята... Они ждут меня, шерин! Ждут!"

traits.speaker: JaeCompanion

languages.text: "I... do..." {n}Something breaks in Jae's voice. It even sounds to you as if you hear a grinding noise — as if an old screw has come loose and the rusty mechanism is screeching in protest at the assault.{/n} "But Torra and the rest... They're waiting for me, shereen! They're waiting!"

languages.text: 「ええ…もちろん.」{n}ジェイの声の何かが壊れた。それは、まるできしむような音に聞こえる。古いネジが緩み、錆びた機構が暴行に抗議して金切り声を上げているかのようだ。{/n}「だけど、トッラと残りのみんなは…彼らはあたしを待っているのよ、シャリーン！待っているの！」

languages.text: “我……我很清楚……”{n}婕伊的话语中，似乎有什么东西崩溃了。你甚至仿佛听到了吱嘎声，就像是老旧的螺丝钉松动了，生锈的机械装置抗议着，发出了刺耳的尖叫。{/n}“可托菈和剩下的人……他们都在等着我呢，亲爱的！他们在等着我呀！”
languages.original_text: "I... do..." {n}Something breaks in Jae's voice. It even sounds to you as if you hear a grinding noise — as if an old screw has come loose and the rusty mechanism is screeching in protest at the assault.{/n} "But Torra and the rest... They're waiting for me, shereen! They're waiting!"

languages.text: «Se lo... aseguro...». {n}Algo se quiebra en la voz de Jae. Incluso te parece oír un chirrido, como si un viejo tornillo se hubiera aflojado y el oxidado mecanismo chirriara en protesta por el forcejeo.{/n} «Pero Torra y los demás... ¡me están esperando, shereen! ¡Cuentan conmigo!».
languages.original_text: "I... do..." {n}Something breaks in Jae's voice. It even sounds to you as if you hear a grinding noise — as if an old screw has come loose and the rusty mechanism is screeching in protest at the assault.{/n} "But Torra and the rest... They're waiting for me, shereen! They're waiting!"

traits.speaker: JaeCompanion

languages.text: « Je... je le sais bien... » {n}Quelque chose semble se briser dans la voix de Jae. Vous entendriez presque un son d'engrenages qui se grippent et protestent, comme si une vis rouillée s'était égarée dans un mécanisme bien rodé.{/n} « Mais Torra, et les autres... Ils m'attendent, shereen ! Ils ont besoin de moi ! »

They're waiting for me, shereen! They're waiting!"

languages.text: "Ja ..." {n}Jaes Stimme klingt, als würde etwas knirschen – eine alte Schraube, die sich gelockert hat, und der rostige Mechanismus dahinter protestiert dagegen.{/n} "Aber Torra und die anderen ... Sie warten auf mich, Shereen! Sie warten!"

languages.text: "Şey... Bil..." {n}Jae'ın sesi çatallaşıyor. Bu ses; bir şeylerin sürtünmesini, vidası gevşemiş eski, paslı bir mekanizmanın gıcırdamasını andırıyor.{/n} "Fakat Torra'yla diğerleri... Beni bekliyorlar şirinim! Bekliyorlar!"

They're waiting for me, shereen! They're waiting!"
